kentik-device-onboarder (1.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * postinst now migrates existing /etc/kentik-device-onboarder/onboarder.env
    files on upgrade by appending the new v1.1.0 DNS keys
    (KENTIK_ONBOARDER_DNS_SERVER=auto, KENTIK_ONBOARDER_DNS_TIMEOUT,
    KENTIK_ONBOARDER_DNS_CACHE_TTL, KENTIK_ONBOARDER_DNS_NEGATIVE_CACHE_TTL)
    if they are absent. Existing values are never modified, so user
    customizations are preserved across upgrades.
  * Bump installer User-Agent to kentik-device-onboarder-installer/1.1.0.

 -- Kentik Technologies, Inc. <support@kentik.com>  Tue, 12 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

kentik-device-onboarder (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Bounded reverse-DNS lookups: per-lookup timeout and result caching prevent
    a slow or broken resolver from stalling the onboarder cycle.
  * Optional explicit DNS resolver via KENTIK_ONBOARDER_DNS_SERVER /
    --dns-server. The value 'auto' probes for cloud metadata servers and
    selects the right link-local resolver on GCE / Azure / AWS.
  * New --verify self-test mode: validates healthcheck reachability, Kentik
    API DNS, Kentik API authentication, and reverse DNS for sample IPs.
  * Sanitize device names to the lowercase [a-z0-9._-] character set Kentik
    accepts so unusual hostnames no longer cause permanent failures.
  * read_healthcheck now surfaces DNS failures as clean transient errors
    instead of crashing the cycle.

 -- Kentik Technologies, Inc. <support@kentik.com>  Tue, 12 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

